**Continuación del Prompt para el TP1 (Onda Sinusoidal):**

> Create a simple and centered page for a specific project view inside a university course website.\
\
This page corresponds to: **Laboratorio 1 – Señales y Espectros – Onda Sinusoidal**.
> 
> It must include:
> 
> 1. A **centered container** with a `canvas` element (use a placeholder box if needed) that will later render a sinusoidal graph.

1. A **"Ver información" button** that opens a **modal window** with more details or explanation about this lab/practice.
1. A **"Volver atrás" button** that allows the user to return to the previous page (e.g., the main landing/TP selector).

> Design should stay **minimalist and clean**, with soft shadows, rounded corners, and centered layout.\
\
Use Tailwind CSS or similar utility styles.\
\
Buttons should be clearly styled, easy to identify, and responsive.
